In the search for the 25-year-old, police say they had found a huge snake they suspected had swallowed the man. CAPE TOWN - A missing Indonesian man has been found dead inside the body of a python.He disappeared on Sunday on the island of Sulawesi, after leaving to harvest palm oil.In the search for the 25-year-old, police say they had found a huge snake they suspected had swallowed the man.The reticulated python, reported to be 7 metres long, was cut open and the man's body was found.(Edited by Zamangwane Shange)